{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Host-less, Swift-Testing native assertion harness for InnoRouter’s navigation, modal, and flow authorities."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing\/documentation\/InnoRouterMacros"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Tutorials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing\/documentation\/InnoRouterTesting\/Tutorial-TestingFlows"],"anchor":"Tutorials"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing\/documentation\/InnoRouterTesting\/InnoRouterTesting","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"InnoRouterTesting","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ships three test stores that mirror the production stores’ public API and transparently subscribe to every public observation callback:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"NavigationTestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — asserts ","type":"text"},{"code":"NavigationStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" events (push\/pop\/batch\/transaction\/middleware mutation\/path mismatch).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"ModalTestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — asserts ","type":"text"},{"code":"ModalStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" events (present\/dismiss\/queue\/intercept\/middleware mutation).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlowTestStore"},{"type":"text","text":" — asserts "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlowStore"},{"type":"text","text":" intents end-to-end, including the inner navigation and modal emissions."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@testable import"},{"text":" is required. The harness itself avoids app-side access","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to FlowStore internals; configure inner navigation \/ modal behavior through","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlowStoreConfiguration"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Event-queue-model","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Event queue model"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each test store owns a FIFO queue. Every time the underlying store emits an observation callback, the corresponding event is appended. Tests consume events in order via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receive(...)"},{"type":"text","text":" or its typed helpers ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receiveChange"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receivePresented"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receiveIntentRejected"},{"type":"text","text":", and so on). A strict-mode test store fails via Swift Testing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Issue.record"},{"type":"text","text":" if any events are left unasserted at deinit."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift skip doc-fragment","code":["import Testing","import InnoRouterTesting","","@Test","@MainActor","func pushHomeLogsChangeEvent() {","    let store = NavigationTestStore<AppRoute>()","    store.send(.push(.home))","    store.receiveChange { old, new in","        old.path.isEmpty && new.path == [.home]","    }","    store.finish()","}"]},{"anchor":"Exhaustivity","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Exhaustivity"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default mode is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestExhaustivity.strict"},{"type":"text","text":": unasserted events at store deinit (or at an explicit "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finish()"},{"type":"text","text":") are reported as test issues. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestExhaustivity.off"},{"type":"text","text":" preserves the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receive(...)"},{"type":"text","text":" assertions but silences the final drain check — useful when incrementally migrating large legacy suites."}]},{"anchor":"User-callbacks-are-preserved","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"User callbacks are preserved"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you pass a production ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStoreConfiguration"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModalStoreConfiguration"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlowStoreConfiguration"},{"text":" into a test store, every hook (including ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onChange"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onPresented"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onCommandIntercepted"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onPathMismatch"},{"text":", etc.) still fires. The test store appends events after the user callback runs, so production middleware and analytics pipelines behave under test exactly as they would in the app.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"End-to-end-flow-assertions","level":3,"text":"End-to-end flow assertions","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlowTestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" subscribes to the inner ","type":"text"},{"code":"NavigationStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"ModalStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s full observation surface and wraps those emissions into ","type":"text"},{"code":".navigation(...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":".modal(...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" events on a single queue. This lets a test assert the complete chain triggered by one ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlowIntent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — for instance, that a sheet-blocking middleware prevents the inner navigation store from seeing any command:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let store = FlowTestStore<AppRoute>(","    configuration: FlowStoreConfiguration(","        modal: ModalStoreConfiguration(","            middlewares: [","                ModalMiddlewareRegistration(","                    middleware: BlockSheetMiddleware(),","                    debugName: \"BlockSheet\"","                )","            ]","        )","    )",")","","store.send(.presentSheet(.onboarding))","store.receiveIntentRejected(","    intent: .presentSheet(.onboarding),","    reason: .middlewareRejected(debugName: \"BlockSheet\")",")","store.expectNoMoreEvents()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift skip doc-fragment"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/innoroutertesting\/innoroutertesting"]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"InnoRouterTesting","role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"InnoRouterMacros"}]},"references":{"doc://com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing/documentation/InnoRouterMacros":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[],"title":"InnoRouterMacros","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing\/documentation\/InnoRouterMacros","url":"\/documentation\/innoroutermacros"},"doc://com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing/documentation/InnoRouterTesting/Tutorial-TestingFlows":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Assert the complete chain triggered by a single ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlowIntent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigation, modal, middleware cancellation, path reconciliation —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through a single FIFO receive queue, without mounting any SwiftUI","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"host.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Testing Flows End-to-End with `FlowTestStore`","url":"\/documentation\/innoroutertesting\/tutorial-testingflows","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.innosquad.innorouter.docs.testing\/documentation\/InnoRouterTesting\/Tutorial-TestingFlows","role":"article"}}}